OL,7,FWhen Robert Boak took his wife,
OL,8,FAnnelies, into hospital with an
OL,9,Finfection in her leg last June, he
OL,10,Fthought she would be back at home in a
OL,11,Fday or two with a course of
OL,12,Fantibiotics. A similar infection had
OL,13,Fcleared up in the past after it was
OL,14,Ftreated with drugs.
OL,16,FHowever, within a week Mrs Boak, 63,
OL,17,Fhad been placed into a coma from which
OL,18,Fshe never recovered. She died 10 days
OL,19,Fafter being transferred from Furness
OL,20,FGeneral Hospital to Salford Royal
OL,21,FHospital in Greater Manchester.
OL,3,C'The way my wife died in hospital after
OL,4,Cbeing admitted with an infection will
OL,5,Chaunt me forever'
